premise_source_doc_sentence: The Godfather Saga is also known as The Godfather : The Complete Novel for Television , The Godfather : A Novel for Television , The Godfather Novella , and The Godfather Epic  (  on HBO  )  .
Salvatore `` Sal '' Tessio is a fictional character in Mario Puzo 's 1969 novel The Godfather , as well as two of the films based on it : The Godfather and The Godfather Part II  (  1974  )  .
Tessio has also appeared in the 2004 novel The Godfather Returns and the 2006 video game The Godfather .
The Godfather Effect is a 2012 critically acclaimed study of the Godfather films - as well as Mario Puzo 's novel - and their effect on American culture .

Partially based on Puzo 's 1969 novel The Godfather , the film is both sequel and prequel to The Godfather , presenting parallel dramas : one picks up the 1958 story of Michael Corleone  (  Pacino  )  , the new Don of the Corleone crime family , protecting the family business in the aftermath of an attempt on his life ; the prequel covers the journey of his father , Vito Corleone  (  De Niro  )  , from his Sicilian childhood to the founding of his family enterprise in New York City .
